Quick NFlick hacking guide
==========================

* Indent is 8 spaces, no tabs
* Please do not put changelog entries into commit messages. Use simplified, human-readable log messages.
* Add yourself to the "Authors" section of the license header of the file you're editing
* Use kernel-style C formatting. Ie.

        if (p == 10) {
                a = 10;
                b = 20;
        }

* Separate function name, arguments, etc. with space. Ie:

        void something (int a, int b);

NOT:

        void something(int a,int b);

* Try to follow the existing code formatting/style/layout. 
* SVN repository lives in http://svn.mdk.am/nflick


